Western Cape cops have arrested a man for possession of unrefined
platinum powder. Cops say in an intelligence driven operation on Friday, 24 June
in Melk Street, Maitland, saw the arrest of a 36-year-old suspect for the
possession of unrefined platinum powder with a mass of 214,98 kilogram. Police spokesman Sergeant Wesley Twigg said: “The value of
the confiscated goods is yet to be determined. The members confiscated machinery
and an undisclosed amount of cash during the search of the premises.” ALSO READ |
WATCH: GP elective conference finally underway! The suspect was arrested on charges of alleged stolen
property and contravention of the Precious Metal Act.  Twigg said once charged the suspect will appear in the Cape
Town Magistrates Court on the mentioned charges.